translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ギロリと――音を立てそうなほど
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: A piercing glare — almost making a sound —

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 鋭い眼光がヨシフを貫いた。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: a sharp gaze pierced through Yosif.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 大将軍ヨシフも凡人ではない。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: General Yosif is no ordinary man.
He understood from his expression alone.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 何があったかは分からないが、
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Though he did not know what had happened,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 今のレキシントンが昨日までと違い、
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: the Lexington of now was different from yesterday,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: まぎれもなく戦士であることを。
おそらくもう二度と晒すまい……）
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: probably will never be shown again...)

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 「おげろろろろろ、えろえろえろえろ……！」
レキシントンがヨシフの足下に
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Lexington vomited spectacularly at Yosif's feet.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 胃の中のものを盛大に吐き散らした。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: He spewed the contents of his stomach all over.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: どうも昨日の酒が残ってるようだ！」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Looks like I'm still feeling the effects of yesterday's drinking!"
"So, what were we talking about again?"
"No, about today's battle... please do your best..."
"? No need to even say it."

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ヨシフは足を微妙に地面に擦りつけながら
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Yosif subtly scraped his foot against the ground

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 「大丈夫ですか、レキシントン様。
やはり今日は休まれた方が……」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Perhaps it would be better if you rested today..."

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 儂の大好きな大好きな戦だ！」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: It's the war I love, love so much!"

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: レキシントンの生きる糧だもんねー」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: the very things that keep Lexington alive."

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 女の体じゃあアトランタも抱けんで
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: In a woman's body, I can't even hold Atlanta,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 不便な思いしとるんだ、戦くらい出させろ」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: It's frustrating, so at least let me go to the battle."

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 「なぁに、酒なんぞ戦っている間に抜ける」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: "Don't worry, the alcohol will leave my system while I'm fighting."

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 復活祝いにまずは人間共を血祭りにしてやるわ！」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: To celebrate my revival, I'll first send these humans to a bloodbath!"

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 「ぬるいぬるいぬるいぬるい！
なんだこの甘っちょろさは！」
この軍一番の者を連れてこい！」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Bring me the strongest of this army!"

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: こないだまでと随分キャラ違うような……」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: He seems so different from how he was just the other day..."

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 「おーん？　その下品な気配は……」
「ほう、本当にまだ生きてたか。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: "Oh, so you really are still alive.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 性格が元に戻っとるのう」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: but your personality seems to have returned to normal."
